<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Taperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Taperus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Taperus</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Onukia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Onukia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Onukia</taxonomicName>
Matsumura, it differs from this genus in having the median longitudinal carina of vertex very weak, nearly indistinct; area between median carina and submarginal carina of vertex nearly flat rather than concave and male pygofer with rows or groups of stout spine-like macrosetae marginally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
